  where he retired his hobbies included hunting fishing and watching his sons play sports in addition to his parents he is preceded in death by his infant son christopher charles townsend he is survived by his wife barbara ann freeman townsend a daughter and soninlaw cris and brian catlett of cabot two sons and a daughterinlaw matthew charles townsend of fayetteville and andrew calvin and tranisa townsend of conway a brother and sisterinlaw houston lee and carol townsend of russellville and four grandchildren abby grace catlett lily faith catlett emerie cate townsend and carter calvin townsend the funeral service will be  am thursday november   at the shinn chapel with the rev fred goates officiating burial will be in phoenix cemetery and under the direction of shinn funeral service of russellville the family will receive friends wednesday evening from –  pm at the funeral home memorials may be made to st jude childrens research hospital  st jude place memphis tennessee  the online obituary and guestbook are available at wwwshinnfuneralcom funeral home shinn funeral service  west main street russellville ar  tel   email us profile of shinn funeral service send flowers send condolences previous send flowerss send food plant a tree in the holy land send a personalized card plant a tree in the us make a donation send a soup gift basket create an oral history support library plant trees in israel memorial cards  bookmarks next search other sources visitation november    pm to  pm shinn funeral service  west main street russellville ar    get directions shinn funeral service  west main street russellville ar  visitation for charles c townsend httpwwwtributescomobituaryshowcharlesctownsendservices httpwwwtributescomobituarygeticsservicetr funeral service november    am shinn chapel  west main street russellville ar    get directions shinn chapel  west main street russellville ar  funeral service for charles c townsend httpwwwtributescomobituaryshowcharlesctownsendservices