ed stomach bitters and the lediard’s morning call bitters bottles in my collection these bottles all come in great dropdead colors lediard  co advertising trade card top of post and here – joe gourd collection here is a partial listing of lediard products c lediard  st louis smith   wilson  c lediard  st louis wilson  lediard’s  celebrated  stomach bitters watson  ring  lediard’s  morning call  stomach bitters ring  c lediard new york ring  lediard’s  ok plantation  bitters –  ring  lediard’s  old dominion  mint julep prg added to list lediard’s morning call advertisement – the times picayune thursday may   lediard’s choice liqueurs advertisement –  alterative tonic advertisement – the tennessean saturday may   lots of lediard brands just received on the louisa moore at kelly’s saloon – the wilmington herald tuesday june   a number of lediard products listed in this advertisement in the southern intelligencer austin texas vol  no  ed  thursday july   hastings lediard  co st louis directory –  hastings lediard  co noting a franklin b hastings and charles lediard st louis directory –  hastings lediard  co noting a franklin b hastings in st louis and charles lediard and jacob and charles berlin new york  st louis directory lediard’s ok plantation bitters advertisement – the galveston daily news wed september   various notes charles lediard was a liquor dealer in new york advertising as such in the new york daily times in  digger odell there was a lediard’s  morning call  stomach bitters advertised in mobile in  antiquebottlesnet a labeled “lediard’s morning call bitters” embossed c lediard new york was found in panama antiquebottlesnet frank hastings and charles lediard were listed in the  st louis business directory selling bitters this bottle is listed as m in the bitters book and looks to be the bottle i have it is embossed morning call  bitters mine was dug in st louis however the book indicates a size of  ″ x  ″ while mine is  ″ x  ″ a six sided double ring applied top bottle embossed c lediard  st louis sold at auction in  antiquebottlesnet a fragmentary hexagonal bottle of clear greenish brown glass for bitters that bears parts of the legend “c lediard  st louis” httpfishhookcsndsunodakedu to my knowledge the only example of the lediard’s stomach bitters discovered in sierra county i watched being broken a goodyears bar digger and i were putting a test hole in the back of a cabin site when he put his shovel through a beautiful teal blue iron pontiled example of this bottle the cabin site above indian valley and on the trail to indian hill is one of several cabin sites that were discovered while walking the area recent extensive logging operations in the area of the trail and townsite of indian hill have pretty much destroyed any traces of the trail and cabin sites that were located alongside of it although this is not a western manufactured bottle collectors believe it was distributed and marketed exclusively on the pacific coast western bitters and gold rush collectors rate this bottle as rare and consider it a very desirable addition to their collection rick simi – western bitters news new addition hello ferdinand enjoyed the post on the lediard bottles i have always been amazed at the variety of bottles produced for his products i was lucky enough to find one of the celebrated stomach bitters many years ago it has been one of my favorite bottles then about six years ago i got lucky again and found a beautiful mint julep pictured below yet another lediard product smooth based it looks to be the same color as the morning call bitters i also remember seeing a pair of the six sided bottles from st louis except they were embossed new york one was green and the other i would say similar in color to the st louis one in your post got to wonder if there are other lediard bottles out there steve mello select listings  charles lediard born in england both parents from england  december  baptised in england father john mother elizabeth  charles lediard segars  broadway h  broome – new york city directory  charles lediard petition to become citizen of united states see below  charles lediard  s william – new york city directory  lediard’s morning call advertisement see above – the times picayune thursday may    charles lediard liquors  dey new york city – trow’s new york city directory  hastings lediard  co  s w hastings  co  – st louis city directory   washington ave   washington ave   n nd  this address also appears as hastings  berlin  washington ave   n nd   lediard  townsend charles lediard and william e townsend importers of wines and liquors  and  murray – new york city directory  lediard  co warehouse and offices at no  pearl street lediard  co exporter of bourbon and rye whiskies florida water bay bum eau de cologne etc no  pearl street the importance of the metropolis as the centre of the export trade in liquors and other specialties can scarcely be over estimated as the increasing magnitude of the annual transactions at the port of new york abundantly demonstrate the wellknown and reliable establishment of messrs lediard  co whose spacious warehouse and offices are eligibly located at no  pearl street was established by the present proprietor in  and since its inception at that period has obtained an extensive foreign patronage principally in australia and new zealand lediards’ defuselized kentucky bourbon “short horn” brand has already commended itself to the trade and to physicians as the safest whiskey for use being endorsed by dr w c tilden chemist united states treasury department as altogether free from impurities and by dr h c bartlett of london as perfectly free from fusel oil mr lediard exports in large quantities bourbon and rye whiskies florida water bay rum eau de cologne zulu water sarsaparilla bitters schnapps etc and his facilities for procuring goods direct from producers and manufactures are unexcelled by those of any other house in the trade all orders are promptly filled and it is the endeavor of mr lediard to merit by the strictest principles of mercantile integrity a continuance of the support he has already enjoyed the bourbon and rye whiskies exported to australia and new zealand have obtained an excellent reputation for quality and fineness at the antipodes and are strong competitors with the scotch and irish honors mr charles lediard the sole proprietor of this flourishing firm is an old resident of new york and is greatly respected by the community  chas lediard liquor dealer age in   birth year abt  birthplace england – united states federal census  lediard’s ok plantation bitters advertisement see above – the galveston daily news wed september    charles lediard importer  new church – new york city directory  chas lediard exporter boarder age in   birth year abt  birthplace england father and mothers birthplace england – united states federal census  lediard’s morning call bitters advertisement see below – new york’s great industries  lediard  company charles lediard exporters  pearl h  union brooklyn – new york city directory the carlyn ring and bill ham listings in bitters bottles if appropriate precedes each bottle lediard’s morning call l   lediard’s morning call bitters circa  –  l…lediard’s morning call bitters lediard’s  morning call  ″ x   round olive green ltcr applied mouth with and without metallic pontil mark the cylindrical lediard’s morning call bitters in olive green – meyer collection lediard’s morning call bitters bottle lediard’s morning call was one of the may bitters bottles shipped aboard the ss republic bound for new orleans the product of new york liquor merchant charles lediard the tonic was advertised as an “invigorating cordial bitter” less than a dozen examples were excavated from the site – odyssey marine exploration cylinder shaped lediard’s morning call in a half gallon size according to lou lambert it’s a wicked light yellow green with millions of bubbles and non pontiled – oldwestbottlescom lediard’s celebrated stomach bitters l   lediard’s celebrated stomach bitters circa  –  lediard’s  celebrated  stomach bitters  f    x      square blue green and emerald green ltc applied mouth without metallic pontil mark – very scarce with metallic pontil mark – rare originated by charles lediard new york ny new york city directory charles lediard originated the tricornered plantation bitters and lediard’s celebrated stomach bitters from  to  charles lediard was listed as a liquor merchant and bitters manufacturer with several different partners note most specimens of the bottle dug in california possibly a bottle made primary for west coast distribution the square lediard’s celebrated stomach bitters in bluegreen – meyer collection ok plantation o    ok plantation circa  –  ok  plantation    motif  vertical ribs  motif  vertical ribs   s  patented  au   oct th    motif window  motif window    x     triangular amber and puce ltc applied mouth ok  plantation    motif  vertical ribs  motif  vertical ribs   s  patented  au     motif window   motif window    x     square amber puce apricot and olive amber applied mouth ltc the triangular ok plantation bitters – meyer collection as consumers in the mids developed a fondness for alcoholspiked herbal remedies thousands of bitters brands inundated the market under the guise of medicinal tonics many of these products made from varied ingredients were sold with vast claims as to the number of diseases and disorders they cured the enormous profits to be had attracted many enterprising merchants such as charles lediard of new york whose ok plantation bitters was found among the ss republic’s assorted consignment of bitters bottles the four bottles recovered from the wreck site were all empty of their original contents listed as a liquor merchant and bitters manufacturer lediard sold a variety of bitters brands including his ok plantation bitters uniquely packaged in a tricornered bottle the bottles was produced in varying shades of amber ranging from lighter to golden tones to darker purplereds during the thcentury as shelf recognition became important for sales packaging became more distinctive more colorful and more influential this threesided log cabin example is rarely seen today suggesting it was not one of lediard’s more successful products yet its scarcity makes the ok plantation bitters bottle a prized specimen for modernday collectors – odyssey’s virtual museum lediard’s ok plantation bitters l   lediard’s ok plantation bitters circa  –  lediard’s  ok plantation  bitters –   sp  charles lediard   new york  x   x    square amber ltc applied mouth  sp extremely rare pair of square lediard’s ok plantation bitters in amber and yellow both extremely rare yellow believed to be unique – meyer collection c lediard   st louis or new york previously sold on ebay for your viewing pleasure today i am listing a rare st louis bitters bottle embossed c lediard  st louis on one panel this is a six sided double ring applied top unmarked “bitters” bottle from st louis charles lediard was listed in ham and ring as a liquor merchant and bitters manufacturer he produced several marked bitters morning call ok plantation and celebrated stomach because of the ornate shape and design of this bottle it is considered to be a early unmarked bitters all the marked examples of bitters in ham and ring date to around  some display iron pontil marks all are listed as rare or extremely rare an unmarked “bitters” in the mold of the triangular ok plantation bottle sold on a american glass auction a while back for around  this bottle has been pro tumbled and has no defects that i can find it does have many large bubbles throughout  interior bubbles are open it also has a small piece of glass that has dripped down and add to the side near the base when the lip was applied just adds to the crudity of the piecewhile we are talking about crudity  the bottle was overblown in the mold and has a huge bulge on one of the lower panels see picture reddish amber in color to my eye with a smooth six sided base the embossing is bold and crisp and i would date it to before  many of these bottles come from south dakota as this one did don’t sleep on this one somebody is going to snap it up these bottles are rare and extremely desirable i would call this a top shelfer at my house act quick and it can be one at yours as well c lediard new york – dick watson collection submitted by steve mello c lediard st louis – past american bottle auction lediard’s old dominion mint julip killer crude lediard’s old dominion mint julep – steve mello about ferdinand meyer v ferdinand meyer v president federation of historical bottle collectors is a native of baltimore maryland and has a bfa in fine art and graphic design from the kansas city art institute and school of design ferdinand is the founding principal of fmg design a nationally recognized design consultation firm ferdinand is a passionate collector of american historical glass specializing in bitters bottles color runs and related classic figural bottles ferdinand is married to elizabeth jane meyer and lives in houston texas with their daughter and three wonderful grandchildren the meyers are also very involved in quarter horses antiques and early united states postage stamps view all posts by ferdinand meyer v → this entry was posted in bitters collectors  collections digging and finding figural bottles history spirits and tagged bitters c lediard charles berlin charles lediard charleston mercury dick watson eric mcguire franklin b hastings jacob berlin lediard and co lou lambert mint julep morning call new york ok old dominion plantation st louis steve mello stomach the southern intelligencer bookmark the permalink ← ok plantation bitters – the “big boys” the northwestern bottle club’s gazebo at the  fohbc reno expo →  responses to charles lediard and his liquor products warren friedrich says  november  at  pm ferdinand some additional in